182 (2) The plan shall be developed to avoid: (i) an
183 interruption in health care delivery in the communities
184 affected by the transition from one to two authorities; (ii)
185 significant disruption in the working conditions or
186 obligations of employees and contractors; and (iii) default in
187 servicing outstanding financial obligations.
188 (3) The negotiating boards may retain, as required,
189 outside legal and accounting services, and other necessary
190 expertise to advise, recommend, and provide professional
191 services necessary to formulate, finalize, and implement the
192 plan required, the fees for which shall be borne equally by
193 the two authorities.
194 (4) At any time, the negotiating boards may retain a
195 mediator to facilitate discussion and propose resolution of
196 issues or terms of the plan.
