253 instructions or to a different arbitrator.
254 (7) An order of the judge of probate approving an award
255 pursuant to subdivision (5) or (6) shall be final and
256 conclusive on the two boards and authorities, including an
257 order approving an award in part as to those matters decided
258 therein. The terms of the award shall be enforceable by either
259 authority, any authorizing subdivision of either authority, or
260 any affected health care facility, by any remedy available at
261 law or equity in the court of probate with jurisdiction over
262 development of the plan.
263 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
